                            <comment id="17277463" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 2 Feb 2021 21:21:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to use python3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17280637" author="michaelsembwever" created="Sun, 7 Feb 2021 19:24:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-devbranch-artifacts/332/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-cassandra.apache.org/job/Cassandra-devbranch-artifacts/332/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Everything around &lt;tt&gt;python3-dev&lt;/tt&gt; looks fine, but the build (console) is complaining around &lt;tt&gt;dh_python3&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;18:49:43 dh_python3
18:49:43 E: dh_python3 dh_python3:176: no package to act on (python3-foo or one with ${python3:Depends} in Depends)
18:49:43 # Copy in the jar and symlink to something stable
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17281966" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 9 Feb 2021 18:54:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah, well, apparently this was always an issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;E: dh_python2 dh_python2:408: no package to act on (python-foo or one with ${python:Depends} in Depends)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Updated the patch to try adding ${python3:Depends} and changed invocation of setup.py from `python` to `python3` since the former on a debian system will build with python 2.7.&#160; I&apos;m not sure if CI will like that, but I&apos;m not sure how to handle that in a portable fashion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We could also just remove dh_python3 since we weren&apos;t using it previously, but the point about setup.py remains.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
